HEADWORD: Jugglery
<hw>Jug"gler*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. & OF.
<ets>joglerie</ets>, F. <ets>jonglerie</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The art or act of a juggler; sleight of
hand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Trickery; imposture; <as>as, political
